Modifications (Apache-2.0 change notice)
----------------------------------------
This file (material-symbols-rounded.woff2) is a SUBSET of the upstream variable
font, produced with fontTools (pyftsubset). Only the icon glyphs used by the
Lessgo app-chrome UI are retained, plus the Latin alphabet/digits/underscore
glyphs required as ligature-input components. All four variation axes
(FILL, GRAD, opsz, wght) are preserved (no axis was pinned/instanced), so
`font-variation-settings: 'FILL' 1` still animates. The full ~5.3 MB upstream
font is intentionally NOT committed.

Regeneration
------------
⚠️ READ THIS FIRST — icons.txt IS NOT AN ACCURATE MANIFEST OF THE SHIPPED FONT.
It is a WANT-list, and it is known wrong in BOTH directions. Measured against the
committed woff2's actual GSUB ligature table (editor-shell-redesign phase 8):

  * icons.txt had 175 names at the commit that built the font (6e7af964); the
    font contains 247 ligatures. Names are listed that the font LACKS, and the
    font has glyphs that icons.txt never listed (e.g. `phone`).
  * `smartphone` was ALREADY in icons.txt when the font was built, yet is NOT in
    the font. The subset build below SILENTLY DROPPED IT — exit code 0, missing
    glyph. So the failure mode is not "the list is stale"; it is "the command can
    lie". Re-running it as-is may drop `smartphone` again.
  * A missing ligature does NOT render as a blank or a fallback box — it renders
    as its LITERAL NAME in text (a 24px `smartphone` icon became a 144px-wide
    word in the top bar). Silent, and ugly.

Therefore: after regenerating, VERIFY THE OUTPUT AGAINST THE SHIPPED FONT'S
LIGATURE TABLE. Do not infer success from a clean exit. Parse the woff2's GSUB
(note: its lookups are type 7 / ExtensionSubst — you must unwrap them to reach
the type 4 ligature subtables, or you will read zero ligatures and conclude the
font is empty) and assert every name in icons.txt is PRESENT. Known-missing at
the time of writing, all of which this regeneration is meant to fix:
`smartphone`, `menu_book`, `smart_display`, `keyboard`, `warning`, `error`.
Two live substitutes are waiting on it and are commented at their call sites:
GlobalAppHeader's device toggle (`phone` → `smartphone`) and its Help menu
(`auto_stories` → `menu_book`, `subtitles` → `smart_display`, `smart_button` →
`keyboard`).

The retained icon set is the ligature-name list in ./icons.txt (one name per
line — keep it comment-free; it is fed to --glyphs-file). To regenerate after
editing that list:

  python -m fontTools.subset <MaterialSymbolsRounded-full.woff2> \
    --output-file=material-symbols-rounded.woff2 \
    --flavor=woff2 --no-layout-closure --layout-features='rlig,rclt,liga,calt' \
    --glyphs-file=<icon-names-that-are-glyph-names> \
    --text='abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789_'

(--no-layout-closure is required: without it the shared Latin alphabet pulls in
every icon via ligature closure, bloating the output back to multi-MB.)

